Package com.landawn.abacus.util

Class CSVUtil

java.lang.Object
com.landawn.abacus.util.CSVUtil
public final class CSVUtil extends Object
The CSVUtil class is a utility class that provides methods for handling CSV data. It includes methods for loading CSV data from various sources (like File, InputStream, Reader) into a DataSet. It also provides methods for streaming CSV data into objects of a specified type.

      public static DataSet loadCSV(File source, List<? extends com.landawn.abacus.type.Type> columnTypeList) throws UncheckedIOException
      Loads CSV data from a File source with specified column types.
      The size of specified columnTypeList must be equal to the size of columns of the specified CSV.
      To skip a column in CSV, set null to position in columnTypeList.
      Parameters:
      source - the File source to load CSV data from
      columnTypeList - a List specifying the type of each column. Set the column type to null to skip the column. The size of specified columnTypeList must be equal to the size of columns of the specified CSV.
      Returns:
      a DataSet containing the loaded CSV data
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the size of columnTypeList is not equal to the size of columns in CSV.
      UncheckedIOException - if an I/O error occurs
